ORAL ANSWERS TO QUESTIONS : : VEHICLES HIRED BY SRI LANKA ARMY : PERSONAL USE
(i) air-conditioned luxury vehicles hired by the Sri Lanka Army are utilized for the personal use of the senior officials of the Army; and
(ii) fuel is obtained for those vehicles from the Government?
(i) whether the approval of the Sri Lanka Army and the Ministry of Defence has been granted for the hired luxury vehicles to be used for the personal use of senior officials;
(ii) if not, whether an inquiry has been conducted in relation to the use of such vehicles; and
(iii) of the outcome of that inquiry?

. . Question ordered to stand down. NARA : NARA : OFFICERS' QUARTERS OF NARA AT TRINCOMALEE : TAKE-BACK FROM NAVY 5944/15
() , ? asked the Minister of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources Development:

(a) Is he aware that the officers quarters which belong to the National Aquatic Resources Research and Development Agency - NARA - situated at Cod Bay, Trincomalee has been provided for the use of Sri Lanka Navy?

(i) whether there is a requirement of keeping the aforesaid quarters, which was to be used by the researchers of NARA when carrying out duties in Trincomalee and its suburbs, under the custody of Sri Lanka Navy when the civil administration has been restored;
(ii) whether the aforesaid quarters will not be taken over for the use of NARA again;
(iii) if it would be taken over, the date on which it will be done; and

(iv) whether the researchers and officers of NARA will be provided with accommodation when carrying out duties in the aforesaid areas, until the aforesaid quarters are taken over for the use of NARA again?
( ) ( - ) (The Hon. Mahinda Amaraweera - Minister of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources Development) , .

: : LOSSES CAUSED TO CULTIVATIONS IN KAMBURUPITIYA : PREVENTION METHODOLOGIES

(a) Is he aware that residents engaged in agriculture in several Grama Niladhari Divisions including Karagoda, Uyangoda I and II in the Kamburupitiya Divisional Secretary's Division of the Matara District have been severely inconvenienced owing to their inability to prevent the losses caused to harvest by monkeys and peacocks?
(b) Will he inform this House of -
(i) the steps that have been so far taken to prevent the damages caused to the aforesaid cultivations;
(ii) the methodologies to be adopted in that regard in the future; and
(iii) the date on which arrangements for protecting these cultivations will be initiated?
(c) If not, why? ( () ) (The Hon. (Mrs.) Anoma Gamage) , .

: UTILIZATION OF ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITES FOR COMMON PURPOSES : THAMBALAGAMUWA PRADESHIYA SABHA 6048/15
8. ( .. ) ( - .. ) (The Hon. Buddhika Pathirana on behalf of the Hon. C.A. Suriyaarachchi ) , , , - (1) :
asked the Prime Minister and Minister of Policy Planning, Economic Affairs, Child, Youth and Cultural Affairs:
(a) Is he aware that the Thambalagamuwa Pradeshiya Sabha is carrying out a programme of utilizing archaeological sites for various common purposes?
(i) how a childrens park was made by demolishing the ruins of two dagabas with archaeological value in Unit 17 Colony, Thambalagamuwa;
(ii) as to why legal action was not taken against it;

(iii) as to who is behind the effort of fencing off the cemetery located close to the archaeological site at Lot No. 576, Folio No. 16, Supplement No. 16, Plan No. Thri 51 at Tissapura-Thambalagamuwa in the pretext of expanding it and the basis on which it is done; and

(iv) from whom revenge is to be taken by erecting a fence by obstructing the road to the paddy fields through that archaeological site after the residents of the area led by Buddhist monks protested against it?
(i) the reason for allowing the local government institutions in the Eastern Province to demolish the Buddhist archaeological ruins; and
(ii) whether action will be taken against persons responsible for that or abetted that, after conducting a comprehensive inquiry into such incidents?
